{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866192275,"sessionID":"ses_286214b10ffeHQQzCVYar8lUNg","part":{"id":"prt_d79dfa173001w2mYjXiCFTTyrV","messageID":"msg_d79def9830019MviX86fnX7lFD","sessionID":"ses_286214b10ffeHQQzCVYar8lUNg","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-9c6b39ec48be4c888edf691946bf31a6","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-021 — CLI build 命令\n\n## Requirement: Build command metadata validation\nThe system SHALL validate that required metadata fields exist before attempting to build the container image.\n\n### Scenario: Missing metadata file\n- **GIVEN** the workspace path exists but has no `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, or `metadata.yaml`\n- **WHEN** the `build` command is executed\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL raise `ValueError` with message indicating metadata file not found and exit with code `1`\n\n### Scenario: Missing required fields in metadata\n- **GIVEN** the metadata file exists but lacks required fields (`agent_name`, `entrypoint`, `language`)\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` specifying which required fields are missing\n\n### Scenario: Invalid build_mode in metadata\n- **GIVEN** the metadata contains `build_mode` not equal to `local` or `cloud`\n- **WHEN** the build command is executed\n- **THEN** Pydantic validator SHALL reject the metadata with validation error\n\n## Requirement: Local build proxy support\nThe system SHALL support custom proxy configuration for Docker builds via the `--proxy` option or environment variables.\n\n### Scenario: Proxy from command line\n- **GIVEN** `--proxy` is set to `http://proxy.example.com:8080`\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` is called\n- **THEN** the build SHALL pass `build_args={\"HTTP_PROXY\": \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\", \"HTTPS_PROXY\": \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\"}` to Docker\n\n### Scenario: Proxy from environment\n- **GIVEN** `--proxy` is `None` and `HTTP_PROXY` environment variable is set\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` is called\n- **THEN** the build SHALL use the environment variable value for proxy build args\n\n### Scenario: No proxy configuration\n- **GIVEN** both `--proxy` and proxy environment variables are unset\n- **WHEN** the Docker build executes\n- **THEN** no proxy build args SHALL be passed to Docker\n\n## Requirement: Build image naming and tagging\nThe system SHALL generate appropriate image names and tags based on agent metadata and version.\n\n### Scenario: Image name from agent_name\n- **GIVEN** `agent_name` is `my-agent` in metadata\n- **WHEN** the local build starts\n- **THEN** the image SHALL be tagged as `my-agent:{version}` where `{version}` is from metadata\n\n### Scenario: Version tag with semantic version\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `1.2.3`\n- **WHEN** a successful build completes\n- **THEN** the image SHALL be tagged as `{agent_name}:1.2.3` and `{agent_name}:latest`\n\n### Scenario: Version tag without semantic version\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `v1` (not following semver)\n- **WHEN** the build starts\n- **THEN** the image SHALL be tagged as `{agent_name}:v1`\n\n### Scenario: Default tag when version is None\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `None`\n- **WHEN** the build starts\n- **THEN** the image SHALL be tagged as `{agent_name}:latest` only\n\n## Requirement: Version increment behavior\nThe system SHALL increment version before build and revert on failure.\n\n### Scenario: Patch increment for semantic version\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `1.2.3` and `build_mode` is `local`\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` runs successfully\n- **THEN** `metadata.version` SHALL be updated to `1.2.4` and saved to `agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n### Scenario: Append counter for non-semantic version\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `v1` and `build_mode` is `local`\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` runs successfully\n- **THEN** `metadata.version` SHALL be updated to `v1.1` and saved\n\n### Scenario: Revert version on build failure\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `1.2.3` before build\n- **WHEN** the Docker build fails after version increment\n- **THEN** `metadata.version` SHALL be reverted back to `1.2.3` before raising the error\n\n### Scenario: No version increment for cloud build mode\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `cloud`\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` runs\n- **THEN** `metadata.version` SHALL NOT be incremented\n\n## Requirement: Docker build context and Dockerfile location\nThe system SHALL use the correct build context and Dockerfile location for the image build.\n\n### Scenario: Default Dockerfile location\n- **GIVEN** workspace contains `Dockerfile` in root directory\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` is called with default dockerfile_path\n- **THEN** the build SHALL use `{workspace}/Dockerfile` as the Dockerfile path\n\n### Scenario: Custom Dockerfile path\n- **GIVEN** `metadata` specifies a non-standard Dockerfile path\n- **WHEN** the build executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the specified Dockerfile path\n\n### Scenario: Build context is workspace directory\n- **GIVEN** workspace path is `/path/to/agent`\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` is called\n- **THEN** the build context SHALL be `/path/to/agent`\n\n## Requirement: Build output and metadata updates\nThe system SHALL update metadata with build results and provide user feedback.\n\n### Scenario: Successful build metadata update\n- **GIVEN** Docker build succeeds with image ID `abc123` and size `500MB`\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._update_build_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** `metadata.image` SHALL be updated with `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, and `build_time`\n\n### Scenario: Build progress display\n- **GIVEN** verbose is `True`\n- **WHEN** Docker build is running\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL stream Docker build output to console\n\n### Scenario: Build completion message\n- **GIVEN** the build completes successfully\n- **WHEN** the CLI finishes\n- **THEN** it SHALL print success message with image name, tag, and size using Rich formatting\n\n## Requirement: Cloud provider build support\nThe system SHALL support building images on cloud platforms when `build_mode` is `cloud`.\n\n### Scenario: Cloud provider specified\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `cloud` and `--cloud-provider` is `huawei`\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._build_cloud` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL initiate cloud build process for Huawei cloud\n\n### Scenario: Cloud provider not specified\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `cloud` but `--cloud-provider` is `None`\n- **WHEN** the build command is executed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` requiring cloud provider to be specified\n\n### Scenario: Cloud build output path\n- **GIVEN** `--output` is set to `/path/to/output`\n- **WHEN** cloud build succeeds\n- **THEN** the system SHALL save build artifacts to the specified output path\n\n## Requirement: Build output directory handling\nThe system SHALL handle custom output paths for build artifacts.\n\n### Scenario: Default output location\n- **GIVEN** `--output` is not specified\n- **WHEN** build completes\n- **THEN** build artifacts SHALL be stored in workspace root\n\n### Scenario: Custom output directory\n- **GIVEN** `--output` is set to `/tmp/build-output`\n- **WHEN** build completes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL store build artifacts in `/tmp/build-output`\n\n### Scenario: Create output directory if not exists\n- **GIVEN** `--output` path does not exist\n- **WHEN** build starts\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create the directory and any necessary parent directories\n\n## Requirement: Error handling for build failures\nThe system SHALL provide clear error messages and proper exit codes for build failures.\n\n### Scenario: Docker daemon not running\n- **GIVEN** Docker daemon is not accessible\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.check_docker_available` returns `False`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message about Docker availability and exit with code `1`\n\n### Scenario: Docker build failure\n- **GIVEN** Docker build fails during execution\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` raises an exception\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print the error message and exit with code `1`\n\n### Scenario: Build timeout\n- **GIVEN** Docker build exceeds default timeout\n- **WHEN** the timeout is reached\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise appropriate timeout exception with message about build duration\n\n## Requirement: Workspace path resolution\nThe system SHALL resolve workspace paths correctly, handling relative and absolute paths.\n\n### Scenario: Relative workspace path\n- **GIVEN** `--workspace` is `./my-agent`\n- **WHEN** the build command is executed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL resolve to absolute path based on current working directory\n\n### Scenario: Absolute workspace path\n- **GIVEN** `--workspace` is `/home/user/agent`\n- **WHEN** the build command is executed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the absolute path as provided\n\n### Scenario: Default workspace path\n- **GIVEN** `--workspace` is not specified\n- **WHEN** the build command is executed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use current directory (`.`) as workspace path\n\n## Requirement: Build runtime initialization\nThe system SHALL properly initialize `BuildRuntime` with appropriate configuration.\n\n### Scenario: BuildRuntime with verbose enabled\n- **GIVEN** `--verbose` is `True`\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime` is instantiated\n- **THEN** `verbose` flag SHALL be passed to `BuildRuntime.__init__`\n\n### Scenario: BuildRuntime with verbose disabled\n- **GIVEN** `--verbose` is `False`\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime` is instantiated\n- **THEN** `verbose` flag SHALL be `False` in `BuildRuntime` instance","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775866192263,"end":1775866192270}}}}
