{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775866216733,"sessionID":"ses_286214b10ffeHQQzCVYar8lUNg","part":{"id":"prt_d79e00111001cRaSkw7EM6nQ0I","messageID":"msg_d79dffb16001mD86CCmjB27RQB","sessionID":"ses_286214b10ffeHQQzCVYar8lUNg","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866327108,"sessionID":"ses_286214b10ffeHQQzCVYar8lUNg","part":{"id":"prt_d79e1afe4001a0B7KGjDvwuC70","messageID":"msg_d79dffb16001mD86CCmjB27RQB","sessionID":"ses_286214b10ffeHQQzCVYar8lUNg","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-d814f7f9a82c43b5b28b2ee434b0f13f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-021 Delta Specification: CLI build 命令\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the `build` command for the AgentCube CLI to build container images from packaged agent workspaces, supporting local Docker builds and cloud provider builds with proxy support, version management, and comprehensive error handling.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Build command registration and default options\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `build` command that builds container images from packaged agent workspaces with configurable options.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Command name: `build`\n- Supports workspace path specification\n- Supports proxy configuration for dependency resolution\n- Supports cloud provider selection\n- Supports custom output path for build artifacts\n- Provides verbose mode for detailed logging\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 1.1: Command registration and default options\n- **GIVEN** the AgentCube CLI Typer application is initialized\n- **WHEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube build` without options\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use these defaults:\n  - `workspace`: `\".\"` (current directory)\n  - `proxy`: `None`\n  - `cloud_provider`: `None`\n  - `output`: `None`\n  - `verbose`: `False`\n\n#### Scenario 1.2: Command option validation\n- **GIVEN** the user provides CLI options\n- **WHEN** options include `--workspace`, `--proxy`, `--cloud-provider`, `--output`, `--verbose`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL accept all valid option values:\n  - `workspace`: string path to workspace directory\n  - `proxy`: string URL or None\n  - `cloud_provider`: string provider name or None\n  - `output`: string path or None\n  - `verbose`: boolean flag\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Build metadata validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate that required metadata fields exist before attempting to build the container image.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Validates metadata file existence\n- Validates required metadata fields\n- Validates metadata field values\n- Provides clear error messages for validation failures\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 2.1: Missing metadata file\n- **GIVEN** the workspace path exists but has no `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, or `metadata.yaml`\n- **WHEN** the `build` command is executed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Raise `ValueError` with message indicating metadata file not found\n  - Exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario 2.2: Missing required fields in metadata\n- **GIVEN** the metadata file exists but lacks required fields (`agent_name`, `entrypoint`, `language`)\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Raise `ValueError` specifying which required fields are missing\n  - Exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario 2.3: Invalid build_mode in metadata\n- **GIVEN** the metadata contains `build_mode` not equal to `local` or `cloud`\n- **WHEN** the build command is executed\n- **THEN** Pydantic validator SHALL:\n  - Reject the metadata with validation error\n  - Display error message about valid build_mode values\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Local Docker build prerequisites\n\nThe system SHALL validate Docker availability and configuration before attempting local builds.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Checks Docker daemon availability\n- Validates Docker daemon is running\n- Provides clear error messages when Docker is unavailable\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 3.1: Docker daemon not available\n- **GIVEN** Docker daemon is not installed or not running\n- **WHEN** `build_mode` resolves to `local` and `DockerService.check_docker_available` returns `False`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")`\n  - Surface error via CLI error handling\n  - Exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario 3.2: Docker daemon available\n- **GIVEN** Docker daemon is running and accessible\n- **WHEN** `build_mode` resolves to `local`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Proceed with Docker build process\n  - Use `docker.from_env()` to create Docker client\n  - Execute build operations successfully\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Local build proxy support\n\nThe system SHALL support custom proxy configuration for Docker builds via the `--proxy` option or environment variables.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Supports proxy from command line option\n- Supports proxy from environment variables\n- Passes proxy configuration to Docker build args\n- Handles missing proxy configuration gracefully\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 4.1: Proxy from command line\n- **GIVEN** `--proxy` is set to `http://proxy.example.com:8080`\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Pass `build_args={\"HTTP_PROXY\": \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\", \"HTTPS_PROXY\": \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\"}` to Docker\n  - Execute Docker build with proxy configuration\n\n#### Scenario 4.2: Proxy from environment\n- **GIVEN** `--proxy` is `None` and `HTTP_PROXY` environment variable is set to `http://proxy.company.com:3128`\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Use the environment variable value for proxy build args\n  - Pass `HTTP_PROXY` and `HTTPS_PROXY` from environment\n\n#### Scenario 4.3: No proxy configuration\n- **GIVEN** both `--proxy` and proxy environment variables are unset\n- **WHEN** the Docker build executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Not pass any proxy build args to Docker\n  - Execute build without proxy configuration\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Build image naming and tagging\n\nThe system SHALL generate appropriate image names and tags based on agent metadata and version.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Uses agent_name for image name\n- Uses version for image tag\n- Supports multiple tags (version + latest)\n- Handles missing version gracefully\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 5.1: Image name from agent_name\n- **GIVEN** `agent_name` is `my-agent` in metadata\n- **WHEN** the local build starts\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Tag the image as `my-agent:{version}`\n  - Use metadata.version for the tag\n\n#### Scenario 5.2: Version tag with semantic version\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `1.2.3`\n- **WHEN** a successful build completes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Tag the image as `my-agent:1.2.3`\n  - Tag the image as `my-agent:latest`\n  - Apply both tags to the built image\n\n#### Scenario 5.3: Version tag without semantic version\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `v1` (not following semver)\n- **WHEN** the build starts\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Tag the image as `my-agent:v1`\n  - Not apply `latest` tag\n\n#### Scenario 5.4: Default tag when version is None\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `None`\n- **WHEN** the build starts\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Tag the image as `my-agent:latest` only\n  - Use `latest` as the sole tag\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Version increment behavior\n\nThe system SHALL increment version before build and revert on failure for local builds.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Increments version before local build\n- Reverts version on build failure\n- Does not increment for cloud builds\n- Supports semantic version patch increments\n- Supports counter append for non-semantic versions\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 6.1: Patch increment for semantic version\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `1.2.3` and `build_mode` is `local`\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` runs successfully\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Increment `metadata.version` to `1.2.4`\n  - Save updated version to `agent_metadata.yaml`\n  - Return successful build result\n\n#### Scenario 6.2: Append counter for non-semantic version\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `v1` and `build_mode` is `local`\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` runs successfully\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Update `metadata.version` to `v1.1`\n  - Save updated version to `agent_metadata.yaml`\n  - Return successful build result\n\n#### Scenario 6.3: Revert version on build failure\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `1.2.3` before build\n- **WHEN** the Docker build fails after version increment\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Revert `metadata.version` back to `1.2.3`\n  - Save reverted version to `agent_metadata.yaml`\n  - Raise the original build error\n\n#### Scenario 6.4: No version increment for cloud build mode\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `cloud`\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - NOT increment `metadata.version`\n  - Use existing version for cloud build\n  - Not modify version in metadata\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Docker build context and Dockerfile location\n\nThe system SHALL use the correct build context and Dockerfile location for the image build.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Uses workspace directory as build context\n- Supports default Dockerfile location\n- Supports custom Dockerfile path from metadata\n- Validates Dockerfile existence\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 7.1: Default Dockerfile location\n- **GIVEN** workspace contains `Dockerfile` in root directory\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` is called with default dockerfile_path\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Use `{workspace}/Dockerfile` as the Dockerfile path\n  - Execute Docker build with this Dockerfile\n\n#### Scenario 7.2: Custom Dockerfile path\n- **GIVEN** `metadata` specifies `dockerfile_path: \"docker/Dockerfile.prod\"`\n- **WHEN** the build executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Use `{workspace}/docker/Dockerfile.prod` as the Dockerfile path\n  - Execute Docker build with custom Dockerfile\n\n#### Scenario 7.3: Build context is workspace directory\n- **GIVEN** workspace path is `/path/to/agent`\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Use `/path/to/agent` as the build context\n  - Execute Docker build in this context\n\n#### Scenario 7.4: Missing Dockerfile\n- **GIVEN** workspace does not contain a Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._build_local` attempts to build\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Raise `ValueError` with message indicating Dockerfile not found\n  - Exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Build output and metadata updates\n\nThe system SHALL update metadata with build results and provide user feedback.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Updates metadata with build information\n- Displays build progress\n- Shows build completion message\n- Stores build artifacts\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 8.1: Successful build metadata update\n- **GIVEN** Docker build succeeds with image ID `abc123` and size `500MB`\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._update_build_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Update `metadata.image` with `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n  - Save updated metadata to `agent_metadata.yaml`\n  - Return build result dictionary\n\n#### Scenario 8.2: Build progress display\n- **GIVEN** verbose is `True`\n- **WHEN** Docker build is running\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n  - Stream Docker build output to console\n  - Show build layer progress\n  - Display build steps as they execute\n\n#### Scenario 8.3: Build completion message\n- **GIVEN** the build completes successfully\n- **WHEN** the CLI finishes\n- **THEN** it SHALL:\n  - Print success message using Rich formatting\n  - Display image name and tag\n  - Display image size\n  - Display build time\n\n#### Scenario 8.4: Build artifact storage\n- **GIVEN** `--output` is set to `/path/to/output`\n- **WHEN** build completes successfully\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Store build result JSON in `/path/to/output/build-result.json`\n  - Include image information in result file\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Cloud provider build support\n\nThe system SHALL support building images on cloud platforms when `build_mode` is `cloud`.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Supports cloud provider specification\n- Validates cloud provider requirement for cloud mode\n- Handles cloud build output paths\n- Integrates with cloud provider APIs\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 9.1: Cloud provider specified\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `cloud` and `--cloud-provider` is `huawei`\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._build_cloud` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Initiate cloud build process for Huawei cloud\n  - Call Huawei Cloud build API\n  - Wait for cloud build completion\n\n#### Scenario 9.2: Cloud provider not specified\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `cloud` but `--cloud-provider` is `None`\n- **WHEN** the build command is executed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Raise `ValueError` requiring cloud provider to be specified\n  - Display message about available cloud providers\n  - Exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario 9.3: Cloud build output path\n- **GIVEN** `--output` is set to `/path/to/output` and cloud build succeeds\n- **WHEN** cloud build completes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Save build artifacts to `/path/to/output`\n  - Download cloud image if configured\n  - Store cloud image URL in metadata\n\n#### Scenario 9.4: Cloud build failure handling\n- **GIVEN** cloud build API call fails\n- **WHEN** cloud build error occurs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Raise appropriate error with cloud provider error details\n  - Display error message indicating cloud build failure\n  - Exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Build output directory handling\n\nThe system SHALL handle custom output paths for build artifacts, creating directories as needed.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Uses default output location when not specified\n- Supports custom output path specification\n- Creates output directories if they don't exist\n- Validates output path type\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 10.1: Default output location\n- **GIVEN** `--output` is not specified\n- **WHEN** build completes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Store build artifacts in workspace root\n  - Save build result to `{workspace}/build-result.json`\n\n#### Scenario 10.2: Custom output directory\n- **GIVEN** `--output` is set to `/tmp/build-output`\n- **WHEN** build completes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Store build artifacts in `/tmp/build-output`\n  - Save build result to `/tmp/build-output/build-result.json`\n\n#### Scenario 10.3: Create output directory if not exists\n- **GIVEN** `--output` path `/custom/output/path` does not exist\n- **WHEN** build starts\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Create the directory `/custom/output/path`\n  - Create any necessary parent directories\n  - Proceed with build process\n\n#### Scenario 10.4: Invalid output path\n- **GIVEN** `--output` points to an existing file (not directory)\n- **WHEN** build starts\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Raise `ValueError` indicating path is not a directory\n  - Display error message about invalid output path\n  - Exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Error handling for build failures\n\nThe system SHALL provide clear error messages and proper exit codes for build failures.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Displays error messages in red\n- Shows tracebacks in verbose mode\n- Exits with code 1 on errors\n- Validates prerequisites before processing\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 11.1: Docker daemon not running error\n- **GIVEN** Docker daemon is not accessible\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.check_docker_available` returns `False`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n  - Print error message about Docker availability in red\n  - Display guidance to start Docker daemon\n  - Exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario 11.2: Docker build failure with verbose\n- **GIVEN** Docker build fails during execution and `--verbose` is `True`\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` raises an exception\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n  - Print error message in red\n  - Print full exception traceback\n  - Exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario 11.3: Docker build failure without verbose\n- **GIVEN** Docker build fails during execution and `--verbose` is `False`\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` raises an exception\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n  - Print error message in red\n  - Not print traceback\n  - Exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario 11.4: Build timeout error\n- **GIVEN** Docker build exceeds default timeout\n- **WHEN** the timeout is reached\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Raise timeout exception\n  - Display message about build duration and timeout\n  - Exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Workspace path resolution\n\nThe system SHALL resolve workspace paths correctly, handling relative and absolute paths.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Resolves relative paths to absolute\n- Uses absolute paths as provided\n- Uses current directory as default\n- Validates resolved paths\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 12.1: Relative workspace path\n- **GIVEN** `--workspace` is `./my-agent`\n- **WHEN** the build command is executed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Resolve to absolute path based on current working directory\n  - Use the resolved absolute path for all operations\n\n#### Scenario 12.2: Absolute workspace path\n- **GIVEN** `--workspace` is `/home/user/agent`\n- **WHEN** the build command is executed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Use the absolute path as provided\n  - Not modify the path\n\n#### Scenario 12.3: Default workspace path\n- **GIVEN** `--workspace` is not specified\n- **WHEN** the build command is executed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Use current directory (`.`) as workspace path\n  - Resolve to absolute path of current directory\n\n#### Scenario 12.4: Invalid workspace path characters\n- **GIVEN** `--workspace` contains invalid characters or path components\n- **WHEN** the build command is executed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Validate path format\n  - Raise error if path contains invalid characters\n  - Exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Build runtime initialization\n\nThe system SHALL properly initialize `BuildRuntime` with appropriate configuration.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Passes verbose flag to BuildRuntime\n- Initializes services correctly\n- Sets up logging configuration\n- Handles initialization errors\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 13.1: BuildRuntime with verbose enabled\n- **GIVEN** `--verbose` is `True`\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime` is instantiated\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Pass `verbose=True` to `BuildRuntime.__init__`\n  - Enable debug level logging in BuildRuntime\n  - Initialize verbose output streams\n\n#### Scenario 13.2: BuildRuntime with verbose disabled\n- **GIVEN** `--verbose` is `False`\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime` is instantiated\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Pass `verbose=False` to `BuildRuntime.__init__`\n  - Use standard logging level\n  - Initialize standard output streams\n\n#### Scenario 13.3: BuildRuntime service initialization\n- **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime` is being created\n- **WHEN** `__init__` method runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Initialize `DockerService` instance\n  - Initialize `MetadataService` instance\n  - Set up logging based on verbose flag\n\n#### Scenario 13.4: BuildRuntime initialization error\n- **GIVEN** BuildRuntime initialization fails (e.g., service dependency error)\n- **WHEN** error occurs during initialization\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Raise initialization error\n  - Display error message about initialization failure\n  - Exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n## Integration Scenarios\n\n### INT-001: CLI to BuildRuntime Integration\n\n#### Scenario INT-1.1: CLI creates BuildRuntime instance\n- **GIVEN** user runs `kubectl-agentcube build` with options\n- **WHEN** CLI handler processes command\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Create `BuildRuntime` instance\n  - Pass `verbose` flag from CLI option\n  - Call `build()` method on instance\n  - Pass workspace path and options dictionary\n\n#### Scenario INT-1.2: BuildRuntime returns result to CLI\n- **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime.build()` completes successfully\n- **WHEN** method returns\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Return dictionary with build results\n  - Include image information (name, tag, id, size)\n  - Include build time\n  - CLI formats and displays result\n  - CLI exits with code `0`\n\n### INT-002: BuildRuntime to MetadataService Integration\n\n#### Scenario INT-2.1: Load metadata via service\n- **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites` needs metadata\n- **WHEN** method calls service\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Call `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)`\n  - Receive `AgentMetadata` object\n  - Validate metadata fields\n  - Handle exceptions if metadata cannot be loaded\n\n#### Scenario INT-2.2: Save metadata via service after build\n- **GIVEN** updated metadata needs to be persisted after build\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._update_build_metadata` calls service\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Call `MetadataService.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)`\n  - Verify file was written successfully\n  - Handle exceptions if save fails\n\n### INT-003: BuildRuntime to DockerService Integration\n\n#### Scenario INT-3.1: Docker build execution\n- **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime._build_local` is called with valid configuration\n- **WHEN** method calls DockerService\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Call `DockerService.build_image()` with appropriate parameters\n  - Pass dockerfile_path, context_path, image_name, tag\n  - Pass build_args including proxy if configured\n  - Receive build result dictionary\n\n#### Scenario INT-3.2: Docker availability check\n- **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites` needs to check Docker\n- **WHEN** method calls DockerService\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Call `DockerService.check_docker_available()`\n  - Receive boolean result\n  - Raise error if Docker is not available\n\n### INT-004: Build Runtime to Error Handler Integration\n\n#### Scenario INT-4.1: Build error propagation\n- **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime.build()` encounters an error\n- **WHEN** error is raised\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Propagate error to CLI handler\n  - Call `_handle_error(e, \"build\", verbose)`\n  - Display error message in red\n  - Exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n## Technical Constraints\n\n### Requirement: Language and dependencies\n\nSystem SHALL use Python 3.10+ and the following dependencies:\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `typer[all]>=0.9.0` for CLI framework\n- `pydantic>=2.0.0` for data validation\n- `pyyaml>=6.0` for YAML parsing\n- `docker>=6.0.0` for Docker SDK\n- `rich>=13.0.0` for formatted console output\n- `packaging>=23.0` for version handling\n- `semver>=3.0.0` for semantic version processing\n\n### Requirement: File locations\n\n- CLI command definition: `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n- BuildRuntime implementation: `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n- MetadataService implementation: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n- DockerService implementation: `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n- Metadata filename: `agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n### Requirement: Exit codes\n\nSystem SHALL return appropriate exit codes:\n- Exit code 0 for successful build operations\n- Exit code 1 for build failures\n- Exit code 130 for SIGINT (Ctrl+C) interruption\n\n### Requirement: Image naming conventions\n\n- Image name format: `{agent_name}`\n- Tag format for semantic version: `{version}` (e.g., `1.2.3`)\n- Tag format for non-semantic version: `{version}` (e.g., `v1`)\n- Latest tag: `latest` (always applied for semantic versions)\n\n---\n\n## Testing Requirements\n\n### Unit Test Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario UT-1.1: Test build metadata validation\n- **GIVEN** a test suite for `BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites`\n- **WHEN** tests run\n- **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n  - Valid metadata passes validation\n  - Missing metadata file raises error\n  - Missing required fields raise error\n  - Invalid build_mode raises validation error\n  - Invalid language raises validation error\n\n#### Scenario UT-1.2: Test version increment logic\n- **GIVEN** a test suite for `BuildRuntime._increment_version`\n- **WHEN** tests run\n- **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n  - Semantic version patch increment (1.2.3 → 1.2.4)\n  - Non-semantic version counter append (v1 → v1.1)\n  - Version revert on error\n  - No increment for cloud build mode\n\n#### Scenario UT-1.3: Test Docker build integration\n- **GIVEN** a test suite for `BuildRuntime._build_local`\n- **WHEN** tests run\n- **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n  - Successful Docker build with valid Dockerfile\n  - Docker build with proxy configuration\n  - Docker build with custom output path\n  - Docker build failure handling\n  - Docker unavailability handling\n\n#### Scenario UT-1.4: Test image naming and tagging\n- **GIVEN** a test suite for image naming logic\n- **WHEN** tests run\n- **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n  - Image name from agent_name\n  - Semantic version tagging\n  - Non-semantic version tagging\n  - Latest tag application\n  - Missing version handling\n\n#### Scenario UT-1.5: Test cloud build logic\n- **GIVEN** a test suite for `BuildRuntime._build_cloud`\n- **WHEN** tests run\n- **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n  - Cloud provider requirement validation\n  - Cloud provider API integration\n  - Cloud build output handling\n  - Cloud build error handling\n\n### Integration Test Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario IT-1.1: End-to-end build for Python agent\n- **GIVEN** a Python workspace with valid structure and Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** user runs `kubectl-agentcube build`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Successfully validate workspace and metadata\n  - Increment version for local build\n  - Build Docker image with correct name and tag\n  - Update metadata with build information\n  - Display success message with image details\n\n#### Scenario IT-1.2: End-to-end build for Java agent\n- **GIVEN** a Java workspace with valid structure and Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** user runs `kubectl-agentcube build --language java`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Successfully validate workspace and metadata\n  - Build Docker image for Java application\n  - Update metadata with build information\n  - Display success message with image details\n\n#### Scenario IT-1.3: Build with proxy configuration\n- **GIVEN** a valid workspace\n- **WHEN** user runs `kubectl-agentcube build --proxy http://proxy.example.com:8080`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Apply proxy configuration to Docker build\n  - Successfully build image with proxy\n  - Display build progress\n  - Complete build successfully\n\n#### Scenario IT-1.4: Build with custom output path\n- **GIVEN** a valid workspace\n- **WHEN** user runs `kubectl-agentcube build --output /custom/output`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Successfully complete build process\n  - Store build artifacts in custom output path\n  - Create output directory if needed\n  - Display success message with custom output path\n\n### Error Handling Test Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario ET-1.1: Test error propagation\n- **GIVEN** various error conditions\n- **WHEN** errors occur during build\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Missing Dockerfile raises appropriate error\n  - Docker unavailability raises appropriate error\n  - Invalid metadata raises appropriate error\n  - Build timeout raises appropriate error\n  - CLI displays error message in red\n  - CLI exits with code 1\n\n#### Scenario ET-1.2: Test verbose error handling\n- **GIVEN** build errors with verbose mode enabled\n- **WHEN** errors occur\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Error message is displayed in red\n  - Full traceback is displayed\n  - Build context information is shown\n  - Exit code is 1\n\n#### Scenario ET-1.3: Test non-verbose error handling\n- **GIVEN** build errors with verbose mode disabled\n- **WHEN** errors occur\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Error message is displayed in red\n  - Traceback is NOT displayed\n  - Exit code is 1\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n### Functional Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Build command accepts all documented options with correct types and defaults\n- [ ] Build metadata validation correctly identifies valid and invalid metadata\n- [ ] Local Docker build prerequisites are properly validated\n- [ ] Proxy configuration is correctly applied to Docker builds\n- [ ] Image naming and tagging follows specified conventions\n- [ ] Version increment works correctly for semantic and non-semantic versions\n- [ ] Version is reverted on build failure\n- [ ] Docker build context and Dockerfile location are correctly determined\n- [ ] Build output and metadata updates are properly saved\n- [ ] Cloud provider build support works when configured\n- [ ] Build output directory handling supports default and custom paths\n- [ ] Error handling displays appropriate messages and exits with code 1\n- [ ] Workspace path resolution handles relative and absolute paths correctly\n- [ ] Build runtime initialization works with verbose and non-verbose modes\n\n### Non-Functional Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Build command completes within reasonable time for typical workspaces\n- [ ] Memory usage remains reasonable for large workspaces\n- [ ] Path traversal protection prevents unauthorized access\n- [ ] Sensitive information in metadata is handled securely\n- [ ] Error messages are clear and actionable\n- [ ] Unit tests cover all major code paths\n- [ ] Integration tests cover end-to-end scenarios\n- [ ] Error handling tests verify proper error propagation and display\n- [ ] Build progress is displayed clearly to users\n- [ ] Build artifacts are properly organized and accessible\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Key Components\n\n1. **BuildRuntime** (`agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`)\n   - Main runtime class implementing build logic\n   - Handles version increment, Docker integration, and metadata updates\n\n2. **MetadataService** (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n   - Handles metadata loading and saving\n   - Provides validation methods for metadata fields\n\n3. **DockerService** (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`)\n   - Handles Docker build operations\n   - Manages Docker client lifecycle\n   - Provides Docker availability checking\n\n4. **AgentMetadata** (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n   - Pydantic model for metadata validation\n   - Contains all agent configuration fields\n\n5. **Typer CLI framework**\n   - Provides command-line interface definition\n   - Handles option parsing and validation\n\n6. **Rich library**\n   - Provides formatted console output\n   - Supports progress spinners and colored text\n\n### Key Algorithms\n\n#### Build Prerequisites Validation Algorithm\n1. Load metadata from workspace\n2. Validate required fields exist (agent_name, entrypoint, language)\n3. Validate build_mode is \"local\" or \"cloud\"\n4. If build_mode is \"local\":\n   - Check Docker daemon availability\n   - Raise error if Docker is not available\n5. Validate Dockerfile exists in workspace\n6. Return validation result\n\n#### Version Increment Algorithm\n1. Check if build_mode is \"local\"\n2. If not local, skip increment\n3. Store original version\n4. Parse version string\n5. If version follows semver (X.Y.Z):\n   - Increment patch version (Z + 1)\n6. Else:\n   - Append counter or increment existing counter\n7. Update metadata.version with new version\n8. Save metadata\n9. If build fails later:\n   - Revert metadata.version to original\n   - Save reverted metadata\n\n#### Local Build Algorithm\n1. Validate build prerequisites\n2. Increment version (if local build)\n3. Determine image name from agent_name\n4. Determine tag from version\n5. Set up build arguments (including proxy if configured)\n6. Call DockerService.build_image with:\n   - dockerfile_path\n   - context_path (workspace)\n   - image_name\n   - tag\n   - build_args\n7. Handle build success or failure\n8. On success:\n   - Update metadata with build information\n   - Save metadata\n9. On failure:\n   - Revert version if incremented\n   - Raise error\n\n#### Cloud Build Algorithm\n1. Validate build prerequisites\n2. Validate cloud_provider is specified\n3. Determine cloud provider API endpoint\n4. Call cloud provider build API\n5. Wait for cloud build completion\n6. Handle cloud build result\n7. Update metadata with cloud image information\n8. Save metadata\n\n### Error Handling Strategy\n\n1. **Pre-build validation**: Catch errors early with clear messages\n2. **Version revert**: Always revert version increment on build failure\n3. **Verbose mode**: Provide detailed tracebacks when verbose is enabled\n4. **User-friendly messages**: Display actionable error messages\n5. **Exit codes**: Use consistent exit codes (0 for success, 1 for failure)\n6. **Progress feedback**: Show build progress to users\n\n---\n\n## Related Requirements\n\n- **AR-020:** CLI pack command (build command depends on pack command output)\n- **AR-022:** CLI publish command (publish command depends on build command output)\n- **AR-023:** CLI invoke command (invoke command depends on published images)\n- **AR-024:** CLI status command (status command depends on build metadata)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-021/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-021/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-021/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775866327094,"end":1775866327104}}}}
